            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#AA">
                <p>[---] the most excellent patron. The order of decurions built [this] with public money, on account of his many merits directed towards the state, by decree of the decurions.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" resp="#AA">
                <p>As stressed by Bivona (1994, 140-141) the top line(s) likely mentioned the recipient of the dedication. Although Bivona (1994) makes extensive restorations, they fit the dimensions of the stone and make sense of the immensely fragmentary text.</p>
            </div>
